{"id":"261857400_The_cluster_hypothesis_for_entity_oriented_search","abstract":"In this work we study the cluster hypothesis for entity oriented search (EOS). Specifically, we show that the hypothesis can hold to a substantial extent for several entity similarity measures. We also demonstrate the retrieval effectiveness merits of using clusters of similar entities for EOS.","authors":["Hadas Raviv","Oren Kurland","David Carmel"],"meta":["July 2013","DOI:10.1145/2484028.2484128","Conference: Proceedings of the 36th international ACM SIGIR conference on Research and development in information retrieval"],"references":["262245295_A_ranking_framework_for_entity_oriented_search_using_Markov_Random_fields","221232849_Overview_of_the_INEX_2007_Entity_Ranking_Track","221232757_Overview_of_the_INEX_2009_Entity_Ranking_Track","221037684_Overview_of_the_TREC_2010_Entity_Track","221037493_Overview_of_the_TREC_2009_entity_track","220515529_Query_Modeling_for_Entity_Search_Based_on_Terms_Categories_and_Examples","200042392_Computing_Semantic_Relatedness_using_Wikipedia-based_Explicit_Semantic_Analysis","29646150_Use_of_Wikipedia_Categories_in_Entity_Ranking","1957152_Corpus_structure_language_models_and_ad_hoc_information_retrieval","256660325_Exploiting_the_category_structure_of_Wikipedia_for_entity_ranking","239574852_Techniques_for_the_measurement_of_clustering_tendency_in_document_retrieval_systems","222399891_The_effectiveness_of_query-specific_hierarchic_clustering_in_information_retrieval","221397490_Evaluating_Text_Representations_for_Retrieval_of_the_Best_Group_of_Documents","221301144_A_rank-aggregation_approach_to_searching_for_optimal_query-specific_clusters","221300053_The_Cluster_Hypothesis_Revisited","221037619_Research_on_Expert_Search_at_Enterprise_Track_of_TREC_2005","220959592_A_New_Measure_of_the_Cluster_Hypothesis","220229653_The_Use_of_Hierarchic_Clustering_in_Information_Retrieval","2633414_Reexamining_the_Cluster_Hypothesis_ScatterGather_on_Retrieval_Resul